President Trump has declared a state of emergency in Alabama due to the effects of Hurricane Nate. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to help alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The federal government will provide 75 percent of the funding for emergency protective measures. Warren J. Riley has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.